<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default has-neutral-950-color has-text-color has-link-color has-20-font-size" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How do child themes work?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>WordPress child themes work as a layer on top of the parent theme. They inherit the design and functionality from the parent. Child themes can customize certain aspects of the parent theme to create completely new designs, without the need to duplicate code.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default has-neutral-950-color has-text-color has-link-color has-20-font-size" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>Can I customize the child theme?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Yes, you can customize the child theme to your liking. However, changes will be lost if you choose to update the child theme when a new version becomes available. To avoid losing changes, we recommend using a code snippets plugin. Developers can also create their own custom functionality plugins to extend or modify the theme. All Blockify themes provide a large amount of action and filter hooks to allow easy and update-proof customization.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
